This "cdcta" (Call to Action) component is designed to let editors configure a 
simple or elaborate CTA banner. They can specify a title, subtitle, an optional image, 
and button text plus link. Two variants are implemented: "default" and "xDemo". 
The default variant typically places the image on the left or right, while the 
demo variant demonstrates a simple example styling.

We used similar patterns from the "hero" or "template" references. We extended 
the fields in the schema so that we have "title", "subtitle", "buttonLabel", 
"buttonUrl", and an "image".

We've tested it for a typical CTA usage scenario.